You are entering a crowded marketplace or you

15
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:03,090
are a part of a crowded marketplace, where there are many competitors who

16
00:01:03,090 --> 00:01:07,850
appear to be similar in the mind and judgment of customers,

17
00:01:07,850 --> 00:01:12,340
then it can be really useful for you to do some research

18
00:01:12,340 --> 00:01:18,260
and look at comparables on pricing.

19
00:01:18,260 --> 00:01:20,610
I'm not saying that you should set your pricing just

20
00:01:20,610 --> 00:01:22,270
based on what your competitor is doing.

21
00:01:22,270 --> 00:01:29,240
I'm just saying that the customer's tolerance for variance from the norms

22
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:30,890
will be lower.

23
00:01:30,890 --> 00:01:36,010
We often talk about this as pricing sensitivity.

24
00:01:36,010 --> 00:01:39,870
And so pricing sensitivity is really suggesting

25
00:01:39,870 --> 00:01:43,920
that, if you bring your price up a little bit

26
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:48,040
and there are lots of comparable offerings in the marketplace,

27
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:53,110
then likely what you would see is you would see your volume decline quite

28
00:01:53,110 --> 00:01:54,540
quickly.

29
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:58,660
And so that's where there is high pricing sensitivity.

30
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:01,500
And conversely, if there is low pricing sensitivity,

31
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,740
you could actually put your pricing up.

32
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:06,360
But you wouldn't see a decline in volume.

33
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:09,120
So this is one of the things that you can test out.

34
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:14,890
